WEBVTT

00:06.966 --> 00:08.676
Previously on
The Summer I Turned Pretty...

00:08.759 --> 00:10.386
Today's open house
has been cancelled.

00:10.469 --> 00:12.138
So I need you all
out of the house.

00:12.221 --> 00:14.306
- The boardwalk.
That's a great idea.
- You should come with us, Skye.

00:14.390 --> 00:16.015
You know, once they get to see
more of Cousins,

00:16.100 --> 00:17.309
and hang out with you guys,

00:17.393 --> 00:19.603
they'll see why we love
this place so much.

00:19.687 --> 00:21.981
- You sure Milo's cool
with you coming with me?
- Why wouldn't he be?

00:22.064 --> 00:23.774
Because we kissed
for, like, two seconds?

00:23.858 --> 00:25.860
Don't worry. I'm right here
with you, okay?

00:28.612 --> 00:29.739
- [screaming]
- You know, I just feel

00:29.822 --> 00:30.990
everyone's slipping away,

00:31.073 --> 00:32.323
and-and the house

00:32.408 --> 00:34.660
is the last thing
tying us together.

00:34.744 --> 00:35.995
[Jeremiah] Everything's gone.

00:39.373 --> 00:41.375
♪ ♪

00:51.051 --> 00:53.220
- [♪ Cage the Elephant:
"Goodbye"]
- ♪ All my life ♪

00:53.304 --> 00:55.389
♪ I read between the lines ♪

00:56.390 --> 01:00.603
♪ Held on too tight,
you know I tried ♪

01:01.604 --> 01:05.608
♪ But in the end
it left me paralyzed, ♪

01:06.942 --> 01:11.155
♪ It's all right,
goodbye, goodbye ♪

01:12.364 --> 01:16.035
♪ Seems like yesterday
I was a child ♪

01:17.077 --> 01:21.664
♪ Just a ripple
in the folds of time ♪

01:23.459 --> 01:26.295
[Jeremiah] It's like
she was never here at all.

01:27.922 --> 01:31.675
♪ It's all right, goodbye ♪

01:31.759 --> 01:33.511
♪ Goodbye ♪

01:33.594 --> 01:36.055
I didn't think it was possible
for things to get worse.

01:36.138 --> 01:37.264
[sniffles]

01:37.348 --> 01:39.140
I was wrong.

01:39.225 --> 01:41.352
- This is worse.
- ♪ Goodbye, goodbye ♪

01:41.435 --> 01:43.020
- ♪ Goodbye ♪
- This is fucked.

01:44.063 --> 01:47.566
♪ Won't cry,
won't cry, won't cry ♪

01:47.650 --> 01:49.068
Everything's gone.

01:49.151 --> 01:51.237
♪ Lord knows
how hard we tried ♪

01:51.320 --> 01:53.072
[door closes]

01:53.113 --> 01:58.160
♪ Goodbye, goodbye,
goodbye ♪♪

01:58.244 --> 02:00.204
What the fuck, Julia?

02:01.247 --> 02:02.373
[Julia] I'm sorry.

02:02.456 --> 02:03.666
This must be such a shock.

02:03.749 --> 02:05.835
I-I spoke to your father
this afternoon,

02:05.918 --> 02:07.711
and-and he and I decided
that it would be best

02:07.795 --> 02:09.672
not to drag this out
any longer than necessary.

02:09.755 --> 02:12.091
I don't give a shit
what the two of you decided on.

02:12.174 --> 02:14.677
You had no right to touch
anything in this house.

02:14.760 --> 02:16.720
- Those were her things.
- Breathe, man. Okay?

02:16.804 --> 02:18.597
- [Conrad] Stop.
- [Julia] Everything's
in storage.

02:18.681 --> 02:19.765
I made sure that everyone

02:19.849 --> 02:22.977
was very careful
with every single thing.

02:23.060 --> 02:24.562
I'm just doing what I have to do

02:24.645 --> 02:25.688
- to sell this house.
- [Conrad] Bullshit.

02:25.771 --> 02:26.814
You could have said something.

02:26.897 --> 02:28.524
You could have warned us.

02:28.607 --> 02:30.609
All you want to do
is fight our mom,

02:30.693 --> 02:32.111
- constantly.
- Okay, enough.

02:33.112 --> 02:34.780
You're not the only one
that's hurting here.

02:36.323 --> 02:38.659
And I'm not the one
you should be angry with.

02:38.742 --> 02:40.119
Your mother
could have warned you

02:40.202 --> 02:41.745
that this was gonna happen.

02:43.414 --> 02:47.293
She just wanted to make me
the bad guy, as usual.

02:47.376 --> 02:51.088
I'm so sorry
that she was too busy dying

02:51.171 --> 02:52.673
to make your life
a little easier.

02:52.715 --> 02:54.675
You know, it sucks
that our grandfather

02:54.758 --> 02:56.051
loved her more than you,

02:56.135 --> 02:57.720
but I'm not surprised.

03:03.642 --> 03:06.312
[Jeremiah] Conrad could have
chosen his words better.

03:06.395 --> 03:07.980
But he's not wrong.

03:08.063 --> 03:10.190
The truth hurts.

03:10.274 --> 03:11.775
All of it hurts.

03:17.031 --> 03:18.657
[Belly] Jere...
[exhales]

03:24.329 --> 03:26.457
What did you say to them,
anyway?

03:26.540 --> 03:27.875
I told them about Shitmas.

03:27.958 --> 03:30.085
I mean, I just wanted
them to understand

03:30.169 --> 03:31.086
why you're selling the house.

03:31.170 --> 03:32.129
You shouldn't have done that.

03:32.212 --> 03:33.422
That was private.

03:33.505 --> 03:34.465
Listen, I'm not going to defend

03:34.548 --> 03:35.633
what Conrad just said, okay?

03:35.716 --> 03:37.509
That wasn't right.

03:37.593 --> 03:40.930
B... I-I can't defend
this either, Mom.

03:41.013 --> 03:42.222
I mean, can you?

03:43.807 --> 03:45.684
[sighs]

03:47.561 --> 03:48.728
Uh...

03:48.812 --> 03:50.940
[Steven] Connie,
come on... No.

03:51.023 --> 03:52.983
Connie.

03:54.026 --> 03:55.110
[line ringing]

03:55.194 --> 03:57.655
Of course,
Dad did nothing to stop her.

03:57.738 --> 03:59.198
Connie, what can he do?

03:59.281 --> 04:01.992
Jere! He doesn't care about us!

04:02.076 --> 04:03.869
[Jeremiah] Our dad
was never going to win

04:03.953 --> 04:05.955
a Father of the Year award.

04:06.038 --> 04:08.415
He was flawed, that's for sure.

04:08.499 --> 04:11.043
But when it counted,
he was there at the end.

04:11.126 --> 04:12.878
Conrad just couldn't see it.

04:12.962 --> 04:14.463
He didn't want to.

04:14.546 --> 04:17.507
And this asshole won't even
pick up my... calls.

04:18.509 --> 04:19.635
- Did you know about this?
- Easy, Connie.

04:19.718 --> 04:21.053
I'm, no, I'm serious.
I'm serious.

04:21.136 --> 04:22.346
- Did you know about this?
- [Skye] I-I didn't know

04:22.429 --> 04:24.264
anything, okay?
I swear I would have told you.

04:24.348 --> 04:26.141
[Conrad] Would you have?
Really?

04:26.225 --> 04:28.060
Because we haven't seen
each other in ten years.

04:28.143 --> 04:29.937
Would a day at the boardwalk
have been enough

04:30.020 --> 04:31.438
- to make you betray your mom?
- Listen,

04:31.522 --> 04:32.773
I know we don't know
each other very well,

04:32.856 --> 04:34.942
but I-I wouldn't have
sideswiped you like this.

04:35.025 --> 04:37.152
Connie, come on.

04:37.236 --> 04:38.153
What are we going to do?

04:38.237 --> 04:39.780
I don't know.

04:39.863 --> 04:42.074
[Jeremiah] My whole life,
I've looked up to Conrad.

04:42.157 --> 04:45.869
He's always been smarter,
faster, just... better.

04:45.953 --> 04:49.415
Maybe part of me even needed
that: someone to look up to.

04:49.498 --> 04:50.957
But a lot's happened this year.

04:51.041 --> 04:52.876
I don't feel that way anymore.

04:52.960 --> 04:54.294
Okay, we can't just leave.

04:54.378 --> 04:55.879
All right?
The house isn't sold yet.

04:55.963 --> 04:57.923
- We still have a chance.
- [Skye] A slim one.

04:58.007 --> 05:00.634
I mean, full disclosure,
Mom's realtor is expecting

05:00.718 --> 05:02.886
multiple cash offers,
all over asking,

05:02.970 --> 05:04.430
no contingencies.

05:04.513 --> 05:07.224
Thank you, Skye, for that
bleak as fuck assessment.

05:07.307 --> 05:08.642
Also, where are we going
to sleep tonight?

05:08.726 --> 05:10.686
I think there are some
sleeping bags in the garage.

05:10.769 --> 05:12.229
I'm not sleeping this house.

05:12.312 --> 05:14.398
Okay, I...
We don't have to. All right?

05:14.481 --> 05:16.567
Okay, well, hotels are
usually all booked up

05:16.650 --> 05:18.193
around this time of year.

05:19.903 --> 05:22.156
I feel like I should... go.

05:22.239 --> 05:24.199
And I'd totally invite you guys
to come stay with me,

05:24.283 --> 05:27.202
but it's
a pretty small place, so...

05:27.286 --> 05:29.371
Yeah, maybe...
maybe we should go, too.

05:31.206 --> 05:32.875
[Jeremiah] They're this close
to giving up.

05:32.957 --> 05:34.752
Don't go yet.

05:34.835 --> 05:37.337
I know a place
we can crash for the night.

05:40.883 --> 05:42.259
- [♪ Brockhampton: "Goodbye"]
- ♪ Was always the loser ♪

05:42.342 --> 05:44.053
♪ You thought it was cool ♪

05:44.136 --> 05:47.765
♪ What's the move?
What's the move? ♪

05:47.848 --> 05:50.058
♪ Love me or leave me ♪

05:50.142 --> 05:52.144
- ♪ I never could choose ♪
- [quiet chatter]

05:52.227 --> 05:53.854
- ♪ Thanks to you ♪
- [Steven] You sure
about this, bro?

05:53.937 --> 05:55.606
- ♪ Thanks to you ♪
- Yeah, sure.

05:55.689 --> 05:57.107
- Quit whining.
- ♪ It's over ♪

05:57.191 --> 05:58.859
We should go home.

05:58.942 --> 06:02.279
♪ I'm out, yeah...

06:02.362 --> 06:03.697
All right.

06:03.781 --> 06:05.574
Here we go.

06:05.657 --> 06:06.575
Huh.

06:06.658 --> 06:07.868
What, you kept that?

06:07.951 --> 06:10.079
Perks of not cleaning out
your wallet.

06:10.162 --> 06:11.246
What if there's
someone in there?

06:11.330 --> 06:12.790
[Jeremiah] It's been closed
for hours

06:12.873 --> 06:14.583
and-and there's never
any night guards. We're good.

06:15.709 --> 06:16.835
Okay.

06:16.877 --> 06:18.837
[beeps]

06:18.921 --> 06:20.297
- [beeps]
- Shit.

06:20.380 --> 06:21.673
Not a great plan.

06:21.757 --> 06:23.008
[Cam snorts]

06:23.092 --> 06:25.886
It's from Avengers. RDJ.

06:25.969 --> 06:27.638
"I understood that reference."

06:27.721 --> 06:29.223
[both laugh]

06:29.306 --> 06:32.308
Can you guys, like, not?
For just two seconds?

06:32.392 --> 06:33.685
Right.

06:33.769 --> 06:34.686
[sighs]

06:34.770 --> 06:36.230
[beeping]

06:36.313 --> 06:38.315
Okay, there's got
to be another way, right?

06:38.398 --> 06:40.776
We can try the pool gate.

06:40.859 --> 06:42.945
Uh, we could also use
my mom's key code.

06:43.028 --> 06:44.446
Wait, are you sure? Your mom?

06:44.530 --> 06:45.823
Yeah, it's fine.
She's the manager

06:45.906 --> 06:47.908
- at the restaurant here, so...
- I mean,

06:47.991 --> 06:49.243
wouldn't she get
in trouble, though,

06:49.326 --> 06:50.409
if, like,
someone checked the logs?

06:50.494 --> 06:52.287
No, no. She works
the randomest hours,

06:52.371 --> 06:54.039
so that alone shouldn't raise
any red flags.

06:54.123 --> 06:56.750
So long as we don't
make a mess, like, at all,

06:56.834 --> 06:58.085
should be good.

06:58.168 --> 07:00.045
[Jeremiah] They won't
even know we're here.

07:01.088 --> 07:03.507
Thank you for not being
on that whale boat, Cam Cameron.

07:03.590 --> 07:05.175
[Belly] Thank you.

07:05.259 --> 07:06.802
- Thanks.
- Thank you, Cam.

07:06.885 --> 07:07.928
- Thank you, Cam.
- Thanks.

07:08.011 --> 07:09.012
[Jeremiah] Hello?

07:14.393 --> 07:15.644
So what do we do now?

07:15.727 --> 07:17.604
Ugh. Could we
scavenge for food?

07:17.688 --> 07:19.565
I need something in my system
other than sugar.

07:19.648 --> 07:21.400
Allow me to escort you
to the kitchen.

07:21.483 --> 07:22.651
Actually, wait.
Can I come with you?

07:22.734 --> 07:24.486
I have really
specific snack requirements.

07:24.570 --> 07:25.737
[Steven] Uh-uh, Taylor.
No, you're coming with me.

07:25.821 --> 07:27.698
We'll fashion, like,
blankets out of, like,

07:27.781 --> 07:29.908
- curtains and some shit.
- [Taylor] No, I'm on
snack patrol right now.

07:29.992 --> 07:31.368
Okay. So?
I need your loudest voice

07:31.451 --> 07:32.578
to scare away all the murderers.

07:32.661 --> 07:34.454
- Yeah, I'm Team Murderers.
- [chuckles]

07:34.538 --> 07:37.291
Okay, fine. No, I mean,
as long as you're cool

07:37.374 --> 07:39.293
with, like, sleeping on, like,
dusty polyester sheets.

07:39.376 --> 07:42.087
- I hate you so much.
- [Steven chuckling]

07:42.171 --> 07:43.714
Why do you need help with this?

07:43.797 --> 07:45.507
- [Steven laughs]
- [Taylor] What do
you need me for?

07:47.718 --> 07:49.720
All right, I think
I know a place we could sleep.

07:49.803 --> 07:51.054
Uh, you want to come?

07:51.138 --> 07:53.307
Think I'm gonna go
with Cam and Skye, actually.

07:53.390 --> 07:55.142
[Belly] I'll catch up
with you later.

07:59.188 --> 08:00.772
Are you okay?

08:01.773 --> 08:03.567
I never should have gone
to the boardwalk.

08:03.650 --> 08:05.652
[Belly] This is not
your fault, Conrad.

08:05.736 --> 08:08.197
There was no way you could have
known what Julia was planning.

08:08.280 --> 08:11.074
Maybe, but she never would
have done it if I'd stayed back.

08:12.868 --> 08:14.203
They fucking took everything.

08:14.286 --> 08:15.287
And you heard Skye.

08:15.370 --> 08:16.914
The house is going to sell fast.

08:17.915 --> 08:19.416
No.

08:19.499 --> 08:21.793
No, it's not over. I mean...

08:23.295 --> 08:25.339
We're gonna figure
something out.

08:25.422 --> 08:26.924
[Jeremiah] Sometimes
I hate myself

08:27.007 --> 08:28.675
for how long it took me
to notice it.

08:28.759 --> 08:31.011
That invisible force
between the two of them.

08:31.094 --> 08:33.679
I wanted to tell Conrad
that he had no right,

08:33.764 --> 08:35.974
that he'd ignored Belly
for all these years.

08:36.058 --> 08:38.268
But it wasn't just
up to Conrad.

08:38.352 --> 08:40.520
It was Belly's choice, too.

08:40.604 --> 08:42.813
So I forced myself to let it go.

08:42.898 --> 08:46.026
There were more important things
to worry about then, anyway.

08:54.826 --> 08:57.204
What are you doing here?
Don't you have class?

08:57.287 --> 08:59.498
Yeah, class got canceled.

08:59.581 --> 09:02.542
Thought I'd come see
you and Mom.

09:02.626 --> 09:04.753
Did Mom get the full-size
Snickers for Halloween?

09:04.836 --> 09:06.338
[Jeremiah] Mm-hmm.

09:09.841 --> 09:12.803
You think Mom's insurance
is going to accept

09:12.886 --> 09:14.221
a sandwich bag
full of receipts?

09:14.304 --> 09:16.098
'Cause that's about all I got.

09:16.181 --> 09:17.724
[Conrad] I'm sure it'll be fine.

09:17.808 --> 09:19.977
If not,
we'll figure something out.

09:22.521 --> 09:24.856
So, how's...

09:24.940 --> 09:27.192
you know, senior year?

09:27.276 --> 09:28.986
It's fine, I guess.

09:29.069 --> 09:31.196
Mom said you got
homecoming king.

09:32.364 --> 09:34.157
Yeah. I mean,
the coronation was basically

09:34.241 --> 09:36.034
preordained since freshman year.

09:36.118 --> 09:37.452
- Right.
- Yeah. So...

09:38.537 --> 09:40.205
You take a date?

09:42.415 --> 09:44.167
I went with Blake.

09:44.251 --> 09:46.878
Oh, yeah. That's cool.

10:00.017 --> 10:01.643
Are you seeing anyone?

10:01.727 --> 10:05.314
You and I never really talked
about what happened with Belly.

10:06.815 --> 10:10.319
Jere, what happened
last summer was fucked up.

10:11.778 --> 10:14.489
I didn't even know that-that you
two had kissed until after...

10:15.490 --> 10:18.910
I was just hoping
that you could...

10:18.994 --> 10:19.911
What?

10:19.995 --> 10:22.247
Give you my blessing?

10:25.167 --> 10:27.169
I can't believe
you came here like this.

10:28.295 --> 10:29.379
You know what?
Just do what you want.

10:29.463 --> 10:30.589
You always do anyways.

10:30.672 --> 10:32.758
Jere, I want to be with her.

10:32.841 --> 10:35.927
And I... I really think
that's what she wants, too.

10:36.011 --> 10:38.305
But she's afraid
of hurting you, Jere.

10:38.388 --> 10:40.557
- Oh, is that right?
- Yeah.

10:40.640 --> 10:42.726
And it's tearing her up
that you haven't responded

10:42.809 --> 10:43.935
to her texts since last summer.

10:44.019 --> 10:45.979
Yeah. Well, I've been busy.

10:46.063 --> 10:47.814
Jere, I don't want you
to hate us,

10:47.898 --> 10:50.692
but I think about her
all the time.

10:50.776 --> 10:54.404
And it hurts, like,
my chest physically hurts,

10:54.488 --> 10:56.740
to not be able to tell her
that I'm in love with her.

10:57.741 --> 10:59.868
[Jeremiah] When your brother
tells you something like that,

10:59.951 --> 11:02.037
there's only one right answer.

11:02.120 --> 11:03.914
Even if it doesn't
feel right at all.

11:03.997 --> 11:07.000
I'm not going to be the one
to keep you guys apart.

11:07.084 --> 11:09.127
So go for it.

11:10.879 --> 11:12.339
Thank you.

11:21.515 --> 11:24.768
[exhaling]

11:24.851 --> 11:27.479
♪ ♪

11:27.562 --> 11:29.064
[Jeremiah] Being around
Belly this week

11:29.147 --> 11:31.024
has made me remember
all over again.

11:31.108 --> 11:33.151
And my genius plan
to stay pissed at her

11:33.235 --> 11:35.904
and keep her at arm's length
is a failure.

11:35.987 --> 11:38.490
So I just keep telling myself
over and over,

11:38.573 --> 11:40.742
it'll never be me.
It's always going to be Conrad.

11:40.826 --> 11:42.452
Hey, Jere, wait up.

11:43.662 --> 11:45.080
Hey.

11:45.163 --> 11:48.040
I thought you were heading
to the kitchen with Conrad.

11:49.042 --> 11:51.461
Oh, no, they have
plenty of hands. [chuckles]

11:51.545 --> 11:54.464
Besides,
I'd rather roam with you.

11:54.548 --> 11:56.383
I mean, I'm just going
to the screening room.

11:56.466 --> 11:57.801
It's nothing special
or anything.

11:58.885 --> 12:00.554
Sounds like an adventure to me.

12:00.637 --> 12:03.515
I mean, we never know what
we'll find behind these doors.

12:03.598 --> 12:06.601
[chuckles]
It's a country club, not Narnia.

12:06.685 --> 12:08.520
Mm, still.

12:08.603 --> 12:11.356
Adventure is worthwhile
in itself.

12:11.440 --> 12:13.817
♪ ♪

12:15.610 --> 12:17.154
[Taylor] So much
good stuff in here.

12:17.237 --> 12:18.280
[Steven] Huh.

12:20.991 --> 12:22.576
What is this,
like Turkish bath towels

12:22.659 --> 12:24.286
and Egyptian cotton robes?

12:24.369 --> 12:25.370
- This is ridiculous.
- All right.
All right, all right.

12:25.454 --> 12:26.580
Go check the Lost and Found,

12:26.663 --> 12:28.373
see if there's any
extra sweaters.

12:28.457 --> 12:29.666
- [scoffs]
- [laughs]

12:35.797 --> 12:37.757
[gasps]

12:37.841 --> 12:40.260
Um... Wait...

12:40.343 --> 12:41.511
Oh, my God.

12:41.595 --> 12:43.722
I could legit be
a Hadid sister in this.

12:43.805 --> 12:44.723
- [laughs]
- Gotta take a photo.

12:44.806 --> 12:45.932
Stop laughing.

12:46.016 --> 12:47.100
This is so cute.

12:47.184 --> 12:48.810
What, huh? New profile pic?

12:48.894 --> 12:50.770
No, it's for Milo.

12:52.731 --> 12:54.316
Sorry.

12:54.399 --> 12:55.942
[Taylor] Can you get out of it?

12:56.026 --> 12:58.069
- [camera shutter clicks]
- [Steven] Yes, I'm out of it.

13:01.823 --> 13:03.492
Who doesn't bother to come
back for this stuff, anyway?

13:03.575 --> 13:05.243
[Steven exhales]

13:05.327 --> 13:07.287
People who tip really well.

13:07.370 --> 13:08.997
I mean, for them, losing
something is just another excuse

13:09.080 --> 13:11.291
to get a... better something.

13:11.374 --> 13:12.918
I don't know how
your mind didn't get

13:13.001 --> 13:14.336
all warped working here.

13:14.419 --> 13:16.505
Careful.
That's almost a compliment.

13:17.547 --> 13:19.674
Almost.

13:19.758 --> 13:21.218
Let's not get
ahead of ourselves.

13:26.014 --> 13:27.641
I guess, uh,
rich people don't come back

13:27.724 --> 13:29.142
for their drugs, either.

13:29.226 --> 13:30.435
[both laugh]

13:30.519 --> 13:32.145
[sniffs]

13:34.731 --> 13:36.733
Oh, this is cool.

13:36.816 --> 13:39.861
- Oh, wow. This is perfect.
- Ah.

13:41.112 --> 13:42.531
[grunts]

13:42.614 --> 13:45.075
It's the most glorious
sleeping arrangement

13:45.158 --> 13:47.494
one could ask for while
spending exactly zero dollars.

13:47.577 --> 13:48.787
Yes.

13:48.870 --> 13:51.331
You do have a flair
for the epic.

13:51.414 --> 13:52.582
[Jeremiah chuckles]

13:52.665 --> 13:54.876
Oh, they left
the projection door open.

13:54.960 --> 13:57.045
I wonder if I can remember
how to work this thing.

13:58.964 --> 14:00.549
Almost got it.

14:01.258 --> 14:02.801
- [clicks, whirs]
- [Belly chuckles]

14:02.884 --> 14:04.052
[Jeremiah] Perfect.
There we go.

14:04.135 --> 14:05.804
- [Jeremiah grunts]
- Ooh. All right.

14:05.887 --> 14:08.598
You ready for
some shadow puppets?

14:08.682 --> 14:10.600
- Uh, yeah.
- Let's do it. All right.

14:10.684 --> 14:11.810
[Belly clears throat]

14:11.893 --> 14:13.103
[Jeremiah chuckles]

14:13.186 --> 14:15.105
- Oh, the bird. A classic.
- Yes.

14:15.188 --> 14:16.940
- It's a classic.
- All right, but now...

14:17.983 --> 14:19.067
- Snail.
- [Jeremiah] Aw.

14:19.150 --> 14:20.652
Wait, that's...
Okay, that's impressive.

14:20.735 --> 14:22.320
- Okay.
- Let me see if I can do,
like a...

14:22.404 --> 14:25.198
maybe like a... wolf.

14:25.282 --> 14:26.992
- [Jeremiah imitates howl]
- Ooh, all right.

14:27.075 --> 14:27.993
[Belly clears throat]

14:28.076 --> 14:29.119
Bunny rabbit.

14:29.202 --> 14:30.870
[Jeremiah] Boop, boop.

14:30.954 --> 14:33.582
- Wolf... eats the bunny rabbit!
- Hey!

14:33.665 --> 14:34.874
No, that is not
how you play shadow puppets.

14:34.958 --> 14:37.085
That's how I play
shadow puppets. [chuckles]

14:38.628 --> 14:40.630
[Jeremiah] When she looks
at me like this,

14:40.714 --> 14:42.841
I can almost let myself believe
she sees me the way

14:42.924 --> 14:44.217
she used to see Conrad.

14:44.301 --> 14:47.178
[DVD menu music plays]

14:49.055 --> 14:51.474
Oh, the... [exhales]
The Apartment. That's...

14:51.558 --> 14:54.436
Your mom, uh, wanted me to watch
that with her last summer.

14:54.519 --> 14:58.273
She said, um, Billy Wilder was
way ahead of his time.

14:58.356 --> 14:59.733
She did say that a lot.

14:59.816 --> 15:02.819
Yeah, we watched
a lot of movies last year.

15:02.902 --> 15:04.029
She'd go all out.

15:04.112 --> 15:05.322
I mean, she'd pick a theme

15:05.405 --> 15:07.198
and watch, like,
three movies in a row.

15:07.282 --> 15:09.659
She'd get a million
different snacks.

15:09.743 --> 15:11.119
She'd drink the green juice
that I made her

15:11.202 --> 15:12.871
with a, um...

15:12.954 --> 15:14.456
- A Twizzler straw? Yes.
- Yes.

15:14.539 --> 15:15.498
- I taught her that.
- Yeah.

15:15.582 --> 15:16.916
- Yeah.
- Oh, my God.

15:17.000 --> 15:19.169
Oh, wait, hold on. Hold on.

15:25.425 --> 15:27.427
[♪ Frank Ocean: "Nikes"]

15:31.097 --> 15:33.308
[Belly giggles] Sharesies?

15:33.391 --> 15:34.309
- Sharesies.
- Yeah.

15:34.392 --> 15:36.311
- [pops open soda]
- Oh-ho.

15:36.394 --> 15:38.396
♪ He don't care for me ♪

15:39.606 --> 15:42.442
♪ But he cares for me ♪

15:42.525 --> 15:47.656
♪ And that's good enough ♪

15:48.740 --> 15:50.492
[chuckles]

15:50.533 --> 15:52.702
♪ We don't talk much
or nothin' ♪

15:52.786 --> 15:56.456
♪ But when we talkin'
'bout somethin' ♪

15:56.498 --> 15:57.915
♪ We have good ♪

15:57.999 --> 15:59.042
What?

16:00.126 --> 16:01.628
♪ Discussion ♪

16:02.671 --> 16:05.298
Movie nights would always
make me think of you.

16:05.382 --> 16:07.175
I'd miss you so much.

16:07.258 --> 16:09.886
And I'd just think
I should call you, but...

16:12.555 --> 16:14.140
I wish you had.

16:15.684 --> 16:17.227
And I would have answered.

16:17.310 --> 16:19.229
♪ I met his friends last week ♪

16:19.312 --> 16:20.605
I would have come.

16:20.689 --> 16:24.609
♪ Feels like they're
up to somethin'...

16:24.693 --> 16:26.903
It would have just
made things harder.

16:26.986 --> 16:29.531
Uh, I should text
Conrad and Steven,

16:29.614 --> 16:31.700
say we found a spot.

16:39.082 --> 16:40.333
All right, you guys,
you can throw

16:40.417 --> 16:41.918
those canapés on this cart.

16:42.001 --> 16:43.503
And I don't think
anybody's gonna notice,

16:43.586 --> 16:44.921
'cause they always
prep way too much food

16:45.004 --> 16:46.214
- for deb season anyway. So...
- [phone chimes]

16:46.297 --> 16:48.425
[Skye] Sounds good to me.

16:49.509 --> 16:51.177
[Cam] I heard
something crazy today.

16:51.261 --> 16:52.971
You know that guy Liam Meyer?

16:53.054 --> 16:54.472
That rich kid
from the East Side?

16:54.556 --> 16:56.516
I heard he bought a Maserati

16:56.599 --> 16:58.017
and then crashed it
two days later.

16:58.101 --> 17:00.812
Okay, so I know the answer
is likely "daddy's money,"

17:00.895 --> 17:03.815
but, um, how did
a kid afford a Maserati?

17:03.898 --> 17:05.150
Yeah, well, that was
a whole other thing,

17:05.233 --> 17:06.943
because, uh,
his grandparents had, like,

17:07.026 --> 17:08.444
this trust fund for him.

17:08.528 --> 17:10.363
He got a judge
to let him access it

17:10.446 --> 17:13.241
a couple of years early.
Boom. Maserati.

17:13.324 --> 17:15.076
- [Skye chuckles]
- He got a judge involved?

17:15.160 --> 17:16.744
Yeah, his parents were pissed.

17:16.828 --> 17:19.204
Cam Cameron, fountain of gossip.

17:19.289 --> 17:20.999
I did not expect
that side of you.

17:22.040 --> 17:23.877
You know, I have layers.

17:23.917 --> 17:25.377
[Skye chuckles]

17:34.137 --> 17:35.180
[door shuts loudly]

17:38.016 --> 17:40.185
Okay. Uh, you go grab
some tablecloths.

17:40.268 --> 17:42.061
- I'll grab some cushions.
- Okay.

17:43.313 --> 17:45.106
Is all this for the debs?

17:46.775 --> 17:48.485
- Yeah.
- It's like... [scoffs]

17:48.568 --> 17:50.069
I can't believe
we're still doing something

17:50.153 --> 17:52.030
that was basically started
as, like, a...

17:52.113 --> 17:53.573
a giant party to present

17:53.656 --> 17:55.867
- a bunch of hot virgins
to society.
- [chuckles]

17:55.950 --> 17:58.745
- It's like... [laughs]
- I don't know, Taylor.

17:58.828 --> 18:00.497
I think you would have
liked being a deb.

18:00.580 --> 18:02.707
I'm sorry, have you met me?

18:03.708 --> 18:05.960
I know you, Taylor.

18:06.044 --> 18:08.546
Actually, I've known you
a long-ass time.

18:08.630 --> 18:11.132
Yeah, you and Bella used to play
princess together for years.

18:11.216 --> 18:14.260
So? You ran around
asking everyone to play doctor.

18:14.344 --> 18:16.429
That doesn't mean you grew up
to be a complete perv.

18:16.513 --> 18:18.139
- [Steven chuckles]
- [chuckles]

18:18.223 --> 18:19.808
[phone buzzes]

18:19.891 --> 18:21.726
[sighs]

18:32.403 --> 18:34.447
- [♪ Frank Ocean: "Moon River"]
- ♪ Moon ♪

18:34.531 --> 18:37.158
- What are you doing?
- ♪ River ♪

18:37.200 --> 18:38.243
Okay.

18:38.326 --> 18:39.452
♪ Wider...

18:39.536 --> 18:41.871
Okay, just imagine this. Yeah?

18:42.997 --> 18:44.249
♪ I'm crossing you...

18:44.332 --> 18:45.959
[Steven] The perfect song
playing.

18:46.960 --> 18:49.587
Perfect guy.
I mean, not me, obviously.

18:49.671 --> 18:51.047
Obviously.

18:51.130 --> 18:53.633
♪ Dream maker...

18:53.716 --> 18:56.052
But your perfect man meets you
on the dance floor,

18:56.135 --> 18:58.388
wearing... um...

18:59.430 --> 19:01.516
[Steven chuckles]

19:01.599 --> 19:04.727
Wearing a suit and a tie.

19:04.811 --> 19:07.438
- [mumbles]
- ♪ That way...

19:07.522 --> 19:09.858
Milo would never wear
a suit and tie.

19:09.941 --> 19:12.360
Yeah, well, Milo's not
your perfect man, either.

19:12.443 --> 19:13.736
Okay.

19:13.820 --> 19:16.489
Now, this, um... [grunts]

19:16.573 --> 19:18.199
...this guy...

19:19.284 --> 19:20.326
[exhales]

19:20.410 --> 19:22.412
[whooshes]

19:25.456 --> 19:27.792
♪ We're all chasin'...

19:27.876 --> 19:29.502
...sees you in your dress.

19:30.879 --> 19:32.380
And he tells you
how beautiful you are.

19:32.463 --> 19:34.757
♪ Chasin' after our ends ♪

19:34.841 --> 19:36.259
And then...

19:37.427 --> 19:38.720
Um, he...

19:38.803 --> 19:40.805
♪ Moon ♪

19:40.889 --> 19:42.515
- ♪ River ♪
- [Taylor chuckles]

19:42.599 --> 19:43.766
You're so corny.

19:43.850 --> 19:45.643
♪ Wider than a mile ♪

19:45.727 --> 19:47.228
Please.

19:47.270 --> 19:50.523
♪ Crossin' in style ♪

19:50.607 --> 19:53.484
He really, really wants
to dance with you.

19:55.528 --> 20:00.283
♪ My dream maker ♪

20:00.366 --> 20:04.495
♪ Heartbreaker ♪

20:04.579 --> 20:07.874
- ♪ Wherever you're goin' ♪
- [Steven speaking quietly]

20:07.957 --> 20:11.377
- ♪ I'm goin' the same ♪
- [conversing indistinctly]

20:11.461 --> 20:12.754
[Taylor] I know how to do this.

20:12.837 --> 20:14.881
- ♪ Two ♪
- [Steven] Look at you.

20:14.964 --> 20:18.092
- ♪ Drifters ♪
- [both chuckle]

20:18.176 --> 20:22.388
♪ Off to see the world ♪

20:22.472 --> 20:27.518
♪ It's such a crazy world,
you'll see ♪

20:27.602 --> 20:29.687
See?

20:29.771 --> 20:31.356
It's not so horrible.

20:31.439 --> 20:36.402
♪ We're all chasin'
after our ends ♪

20:37.695 --> 20:42.450
♪ Chasin' after our ends ♪

20:42.533 --> 20:45.244
♪ Life's just around the bend ♪

20:46.287 --> 20:48.498
♪ My friend ♪

20:48.581 --> 20:52.210
♪ Moon river ♪

20:52.293 --> 20:55.588
♪ And me ♪♪

20:55.672 --> 20:57.674
[projector whirring]

21:03.680 --> 21:04.847
[Jeremiah] Whoa.

21:04.931 --> 21:06.766
You guys weren't messing around.

21:06.849 --> 21:08.059
- Yeah, well, just be careful.
- Oh, I will.

21:08.142 --> 21:09.352
I got it. Don't worry.

21:09.435 --> 21:12.563
Hey, have you heard
from Taylor and Steven?

21:13.690 --> 21:15.066
No. I can go look for him.

21:15.108 --> 21:16.693
[Cam] Are these the canapés
you had in mind?

21:16.776 --> 21:18.820
[soft chuckle]

21:18.903 --> 21:20.530
Yeah, I'll-I'll come with you.

21:21.823 --> 21:22.991
- [Cam] I can't get it open.
- [Skye] Oh, no.

21:23.074 --> 21:24.158
- [Cam stammers]
- [Skye] That's okay.

21:24.242 --> 21:25.159
I'll get it. I'll clean it.

21:25.243 --> 21:26.577
- I promise.
- [Cam] Thank you.

21:26.661 --> 21:27.870
[Skye] Sorry.

21:27.954 --> 21:29.330
[Conrad whistles]

21:29.414 --> 21:31.374
[Jeremiah] Steve-oh!

21:31.457 --> 21:33.626
Did you know Liam Meyer
got a judge involved

21:33.710 --> 21:35.795
to help him access his trust?

21:35.878 --> 21:37.547
Boy, I bet that turned out well.

21:37.630 --> 21:38.840
[chuckles]

21:38.923 --> 21:41.467
Yeah, but...

21:41.551 --> 21:43.261
if a guy like
that can do it...

21:43.344 --> 21:44.345
so could we.

21:45.430 --> 21:47.223
Do what, Connie?

21:47.306 --> 21:50.143
You really want to, like,
sue Dad or something?

21:50.226 --> 21:51.978
I don't know.

21:52.061 --> 21:54.313
- Maybe.
- [sighs]

21:54.397 --> 21:56.024
He refuses to fight
Aunt Julia on this.

21:57.108 --> 21:59.694
And I already told him
I'm not giving up

21:59.777 --> 22:01.571
until I save this house.

22:01.654 --> 22:03.990
Hey, at least,
you know, we're not alone.

22:05.199 --> 22:08.286
It's kind of nice having...

22:08.369 --> 22:10.580
everyone around.

22:10.663 --> 22:11.873
You know,
kind of feels like old times.

22:11.956 --> 22:12.957
[Conrad] I know.

22:14.417 --> 22:17.587
It's good seeing you and Belly
get along again.

22:17.670 --> 22:20.131
I know she missed
having you as a friend.

22:21.799 --> 22:23.801
♪ ♪

22:23.885 --> 22:25.803
[Belly] Wow, I feel like
I'm in a holiday movie.

22:25.887 --> 22:28.765
[Jeremiah] You know Mom.
She loves a theme.

22:28.848 --> 22:31.017
[Belly] I'm glad we all get
to celebrate together this year.

22:31.100 --> 22:32.268
You know?

22:33.269 --> 22:35.563
Yeah, for sure.

22:35.646 --> 22:37.190
- [Steven] Wow.
- [Susannah chuckles]

22:37.273 --> 22:39.484
Look at this amazing table.

22:39.567 --> 22:41.402
Martha Stewart can kiss my ass.

22:41.486 --> 22:43.780
[laughs] I love it
when you swear.

22:43.863 --> 22:45.782
Uh, uh, "ass" is not swearing.

22:45.865 --> 22:47.867
- Susannah, say "motherfucker."
- Steven.

22:47.950 --> 22:50.495
- What? You said you loved it.
- She motherfucking loves it.

22:50.578 --> 22:52.538
Everybody sit down, please.

22:52.622 --> 22:53.956
The food's getting cold.

22:54.957 --> 22:56.334
[Susannah exhales]

22:57.335 --> 22:58.920
- [Conrad clears throat]
- [clears throat]

22:59.003 --> 23:00.546
[Susannah] So let's go
around the table

23:00.630 --> 23:03.341
and everyone say one thing
they're thankful for.

23:03.424 --> 23:04.509
Jere-bear?

23:05.968 --> 23:08.096
Uh, I'll go last.

23:08.179 --> 23:09.430
How about that?

23:10.473 --> 23:12.558
[laughter]

23:12.642 --> 23:13.935
No, he caught me,
he caught me putting sugar

23:14.018 --> 23:15.103
in his green juice.

23:15.186 --> 23:17.313
Okay, Mom, you're ruining
my healthy recipes.

23:17.396 --> 23:18.648
It is culinary blasphemy.

23:18.731 --> 23:20.566
Not ruining. Enhancing.

23:20.650 --> 23:22.902
- [laughter]
- Yeah, like the moussaka?

23:22.985 --> 23:24.362
Hey, I still say
it tastes better

23:24.445 --> 23:25.613
with little pieces
of hot dog in it.

23:25.696 --> 23:27.406
Ooh, Beck, no. If you're
going to ruin a recipe,

23:27.490 --> 23:28.407
ruin it with steak.

23:28.491 --> 23:30.660
[laughter]

23:30.743 --> 23:31.744
[Jeremiah] Does he know
how badly

23:31.828 --> 23:33.996
I've wanted to take Belly's hand
like that?

23:35.039 --> 23:36.165
Would he care?

23:36.249 --> 23:37.458
[Susannah] When Jere was little,

23:37.542 --> 23:39.335
he made
these amazing sandwiches.

23:39.418 --> 23:41.045
- And Conrad...
- [Conrad] Mom, no.

23:41.129 --> 23:42.505
...Conrad, whose
sandwich-making skills

23:42.588 --> 23:44.298
were PB and J at best,

23:44.382 --> 23:46.008
he convinced Jere that, uh,

23:46.092 --> 23:47.760
- crust made your hair curly.
- Mm-hmm.

23:47.844 --> 23:50.346
Oh, dude, that's right. Because
you wanted straight hair.

23:50.429 --> 23:51.556
- Yeah. Yeah.
- Yeah.

23:51.639 --> 23:53.599
So Jere never touched
his sandwiches...

23:53.683 --> 23:55.643
- [Susannah] Never.
- ...and Conrad
finished them off.

23:55.726 --> 23:56.769
Oh. Devious.

23:56.853 --> 23:57.937
You got me back, though.

23:58.020 --> 23:59.981
Remember when you peed
in my lunchbox?

24:00.064 --> 24:01.858
Yeah, let's not talk
about that. [chuckles]

24:01.941 --> 24:03.025
[laughter]

24:03.109 --> 24:04.068
- Okay.
- [Adam] Let's talk about it.

24:04.152 --> 24:05.987
[indistinct chatter]

24:06.070 --> 24:07.780
♪ ♪

24:10.241 --> 24:12.827
[Belly and Conrad chuckling]

24:12.910 --> 24:15.872
Uh, are you ready
for board games?

24:15.955 --> 24:18.457
I'm... I'm too full.

24:18.541 --> 24:20.835
[Laurel laughing] Come here.
Belly, come up here.

24:20.918 --> 24:23.212
Beck found a bunch of 90s
clothes she wants you to try on.

24:23.296 --> 24:24.422
I still haven't gotten through

24:24.505 --> 24:25.882
the last batch
of Susanna's baby tees.

24:25.965 --> 24:27.675
I really don't know
how I feel about

24:27.758 --> 24:30.303
you wearing my mom's
baby tees from college.

24:30.386 --> 24:32.889
[Laurel] There's a lot of plaid.
And ratty Oasis T-shirts

24:32.972 --> 24:34.891
- she stole from me!
- [Susannah] Don't listen
to her.

24:34.974 --> 24:36.017
This stuff is gold.

24:36.100 --> 24:37.935
[Belly laughs]

24:38.936 --> 24:40.605
Yeah, Steven's setting up
the Wii in the other room

24:40.688 --> 24:42.148
- if you want to play
some games.
- Nah, I'm going to

24:42.231 --> 24:43.900
call it a night.

24:43.983 --> 24:45.651
Okay.

24:45.735 --> 24:48.070
Uh, actually...

24:48.154 --> 24:49.488
can I talk to you for a sec?

24:49.572 --> 24:51.407
Yeah, what's up?

24:52.450 --> 24:53.659
Next time Belly is coming over,

24:53.743 --> 24:55.578
can you give me a heads-up
or something?

24:55.661 --> 24:56.913
What do you mean?

24:56.996 --> 24:58.831
I thought you knew
everybody was coming over.

24:58.915 --> 25:01.667
Yeah, I did. But if you guys are
going to be here together,

25:01.751 --> 25:03.628
then I don't want to be around.

25:03.711 --> 25:05.588
Jere, come on.
It's Thanksgiving.

25:05.671 --> 25:07.757
- Of course we're...
- No, it's better for everyone

25:07.840 --> 25:10.426
if we just keep
some distance, okay?

25:10.509 --> 25:12.595
You do your thing
and I'll do mine.

25:13.596 --> 25:15.306
Sure.

25:17.725 --> 25:19.310
If that's what you want.

25:22.939 --> 25:24.482
[Jeremiah] Good night.

25:25.524 --> 25:26.943
[music playing in distance]

25:27.026 --> 25:28.527
You hear music?

25:28.611 --> 25:30.071
- Yeah.
- [♪ Daniel Caesar:
"Do You Like Me?"]

25:30.154 --> 25:32.782
♪ But I gotta know ♪

25:35.034 --> 25:38.663
♪ Do you really like me?
Do you really like me ♪

25:38.746 --> 25:41.082
♪ Low on time, I'd like to...

25:41.165 --> 25:43.042
- Oh, my God.
- Ow.

25:43.125 --> 25:44.293
Oh, I'm sorry.

25:44.377 --> 25:46.337
I hope we didn't
interrupt anything.

25:46.420 --> 25:47.964
No, you didn't
interrupt anything.

25:48.047 --> 25:49.257
♪ Do you really like me...

25:49.340 --> 25:51.926
Yeah, uh, we were
just talking about, um,

25:52.009 --> 25:54.762
you know, the-the deb ball,
and, um, I figured I would just

25:54.845 --> 25:56.973
show Taylor some moves.

25:57.056 --> 25:58.474
I mean, they drilled them
so deep into our head,

25:58.557 --> 26:00.935
they're pretty hard
to forget, right?

26:02.270 --> 26:04.188
[both] Yeah.

26:04.272 --> 26:06.023
- [song shuts off]
- [Taylor] Were you guys looking

26:06.107 --> 26:07.525
for something specific?

26:07.608 --> 26:09.610
We were specifically
looking for you.

26:09.694 --> 26:10.903
We found a place to sleep.

26:10.987 --> 26:12.697
I-I've been texting you, but...

26:12.780 --> 26:15.491
That's-that's-that's my fault.
Just...

26:15.574 --> 26:17.952
- Shoddy reception.
- Oh.
- Mm.

26:23.833 --> 26:25.376
...set in here?

26:25.459 --> 26:27.169
- You play gin rummy?
- This is her favorite part.

26:27.253 --> 26:28.546
[Fran] I'm not very good at it.

26:28.629 --> 26:30.631
[Baxter] I am.
Let me get the cards.

26:30.715 --> 26:32.633
[Fran] You don't have
to entertain me, Mr. Baxter.

26:32.717 --> 26:33.801
[Baxter] There's nothing
I'd like better.

26:33.884 --> 26:36.095
You know, uh, togetherness.

26:36.178 --> 26:38.014
- Guess what I did
last Christmas?
- Whoa, whoa.

26:38.097 --> 26:39.390
There's extra napkins
if you need them.

26:39.473 --> 26:40.433
Thank you.

26:40.516 --> 26:41.892
I'll take one.

26:41.976 --> 26:42.935
[Baxter] ...then I came home
and cleaned up

26:43.019 --> 26:44.437
after Mr. Eichelberger.

26:44.520 --> 26:47.023
He had a little
eggnog party here.

26:47.106 --> 26:48.983
So I'm way ahead this year.

26:49.066 --> 26:51.986
Ah, three across,
spades double,

26:52.069 --> 26:53.404
high deals.

26:54.697 --> 26:56.866
Six, eight.

26:58.034 --> 27:00.036
[Taylor grunts]

27:01.203 --> 27:02.621
Taylor, that's gross.

27:02.705 --> 27:04.290
No, I saw a TikTok about this.

27:04.373 --> 27:06.334
You just poke a couple holes

27:06.417 --> 27:08.544
so that the smoke is, uh,
able to pass through

27:08.627 --> 27:10.254
and then you just...

27:11.255 --> 27:12.465
Yeah, but you can't just...

27:12.548 --> 27:14.175
you can't just
smoke random weed.

27:14.258 --> 27:15.551
Belly, it's not random weed.

27:15.634 --> 27:17.428
It's Lost and Found
rich people weed.

27:17.511 --> 27:20.014
It's probably really good.

27:21.098 --> 27:23.309
- Can you hand me another one?
- [Belly] Yeah.

27:23.392 --> 27:25.144
Well, you need any help,
Tay Tay?

27:25.227 --> 27:27.396
Could you just give me
a minute? Damn.

27:28.731 --> 27:29.940
Okay, c...

27:30.024 --> 27:31.609
can you just be
a little more neat, please?

27:31.692 --> 27:33.069
Also, you can't smoke in here.

27:33.152 --> 27:34.653
- The upholstery...
- [laughing]

27:34.737 --> 27:36.072
I'm not going to smoke in here.

27:36.155 --> 27:37.073
[Fran] What do you call it
when somebody...

27:37.156 --> 27:38.115
[Jeremiah] All right, uh, well,

27:38.199 --> 27:39.700
why don't we take this outside

27:39.784 --> 27:43.662
before Cam Cameron has a stroke?

27:43.746 --> 27:46.040
- [indistinct shouting]
- [Cam] I'm hitting the gas!

27:46.123 --> 27:47.625
- [Steven] Oh, yeah!
- [Jeremiah] Oh, come on.

27:47.708 --> 27:50.044
[Cam] Doesn't really... It's
not supposed to go that fast.

27:50.127 --> 27:52.171
♪ ♪

27:52.254 --> 27:54.173
[Cam] Can you try and be
a little quiet?

27:54.256 --> 27:56.592
'Cause we're actually not even
supposed to be out here.

27:56.675 --> 27:58.928
- Come on, hit the gas!
- I'm hitting the gas.

27:59.011 --> 28:00.721
Wait, guys, guys, guys.

28:00.805 --> 28:02.306
I think I know
what the problem is, man.

28:02.390 --> 28:04.183
- What?
- I think there's
too many of us on here.

28:04.266 --> 28:05.601
- Oh!
- Yeah, yeah, yeah.

28:05.684 --> 28:06.769
That makes sense.

28:06.852 --> 28:08.729
- [laughter]
- Oh! Comin' for you.

28:08.813 --> 28:11.065
- You are so gonna pay for that.
- Go, go, go!

28:11.148 --> 28:12.900
- [shouting]
- All right, all right.

28:12.983 --> 28:14.193
All right, all right.

28:15.277 --> 28:17.655
- Should've stayed inside.
- Need some help?

28:17.738 --> 28:19.407
This is so annoying.

28:19.490 --> 28:21.575
Weed is not supposed
to be this difficult.

28:21.659 --> 28:22.660
I mean, it's like...

28:22.743 --> 28:24.703
Can I give it a shot?

28:24.787 --> 28:26.372
- Yeah. Have at it.
- Thanks.

28:26.455 --> 28:27.998
[Cam] Be gentle.

28:28.082 --> 28:29.583
[laughs]

28:29.667 --> 28:31.085
- [Cam] Come on.
- [Jeremiah] Oh, you want help?

28:31.168 --> 28:32.545
[Taylor] What?

28:32.628 --> 28:34.588
- What was that look?
- Mm.

28:34.672 --> 28:37.216
You and Steven. It just...

28:37.299 --> 28:38.884
seems like
there's kind of a vibe.

28:38.968 --> 28:40.094
No, there's no vibe.

28:40.177 --> 28:43.722
I save all my...
all my vibing for Milo.

28:45.933 --> 28:46.934
Okay.

28:48.644 --> 28:50.604
Steven really hurt me last year.

28:50.688 --> 28:52.356
It's just...
It's not the kind of hurt

28:52.440 --> 28:53.732
that just goes away easily.

28:53.816 --> 28:54.817
You know?

28:55.860 --> 28:57.820
- [Belly] Yeah.
- Or, like, ever, maybe.

28:57.903 --> 28:59.405
Yeah, I get it.

29:02.491 --> 29:03.701
I know you do.

29:04.869 --> 29:07.455
I think I... I loved Conrad

29:07.538 --> 29:10.833
longer and truer
than anyone in my whole life.

29:10.916 --> 29:14.795
And I'll probably never
love anyone like that again.

29:17.298 --> 29:19.216
To be honest,
it's kind of a relief.

29:19.300 --> 29:22.386
'Cause I don't know, I don't
know if I could survive that.

29:22.470 --> 29:24.972
[Taylor and Belly laughing]

29:25.055 --> 29:26.390
[Taylor] Can we make a pact?

29:27.391 --> 29:30.227
Can we just leave
first love in the past?

29:30.311 --> 29:32.062
Like, where it belongs?

29:32.146 --> 29:34.982
Yeah. Yes. Yes.

29:35.065 --> 29:37.234
[both laugh]

29:37.318 --> 29:40.571
I saw you and Jeremy
on the boardwalk.

29:40.654 --> 29:42.656
And tonight on the couch.

29:43.908 --> 29:44.992
There's something there.

29:45.075 --> 29:46.869
Doesn't matter
how far apart you sit, you know?

29:46.952 --> 29:47.953
It's there.

29:49.246 --> 29:51.373
Yeah, I feel like there...

29:51.457 --> 29:52.708
there could be something,
you know?

29:52.791 --> 29:54.835
- Mm-hmm.
- Like this charge

29:54.919 --> 29:57.046
building between us.

29:57.129 --> 29:59.798
But, you know,
then he reminds me

29:59.882 --> 30:02.092
how much I hurt him before.

30:02.176 --> 30:03.928
I don't know. I'm like...

30:04.011 --> 30:06.680
I shouldn't even be thinking
about him like that.

30:09.266 --> 30:11.477
[Skye] Mm-hmm.
Almost got it.

30:13.020 --> 30:15.231
[boys grunting, laughing]

30:15.272 --> 30:16.607
Push, push!

30:16.690 --> 30:18.817
- Put your back into it!
- Oh, God!

30:18.901 --> 30:22.988
All right. All right,
this thing is officially dead.

30:23.072 --> 30:25.074
Why don't we crash up there
for the night?

30:25.157 --> 30:27.076
Well, that would be
perfect timing,

30:27.159 --> 30:30.329
because I have discovered
the secret of the apple bong.

30:30.412 --> 30:31.747
Good job, Skye.

30:31.830 --> 30:33.249
You know, that's surprising.

30:33.332 --> 30:35.501
I have layers.

30:37.461 --> 30:39.213
Great.

30:39.296 --> 30:40.506
Start unpacking.

30:40.548 --> 30:43.217
[indistinct chatter]

30:43.300 --> 30:47.137
Taylor, volleyball camp
is in four days.

30:50.140 --> 30:52.017
It's not like
they're going to drug test us.

30:52.059 --> 30:54.812
Coach would have had to put
that in her email, right?

30:54.895 --> 30:56.313
What email?

30:56.397 --> 30:57.940
The one that we got
yesterday about camp.

30:58.023 --> 30:59.567
Have you talked to Coach yet?

30:59.650 --> 31:01.986
Um...

31:02.069 --> 31:04.280
- No, not yet.
- Belly, wait. Why?

31:04.363 --> 31:05.823
I swear to God,
if you bail on us again...

31:05.906 --> 31:07.658
No, no, no. I'm not bailing.
I want to go.

31:07.741 --> 31:10.661
Okay, well, don't tell me.
Tell Coach that.

31:10.744 --> 31:12.538
Okay.

31:12.621 --> 31:14.540
Okay, yeah.
I'll text her right now.

31:14.623 --> 31:16.542
- Yeah. Great. Here.
- [Belly] All right.

31:22.631 --> 31:25.509
You know, I-I...
I really just don't want to...

31:25.593 --> 31:27.303
I don't want to have
to have a big conversation

31:27.386 --> 31:29.096
with her about last season,

31:29.179 --> 31:32.141
and, I don't know, I feel like

31:32.224 --> 31:33.642
I just want to show up
ready to play

31:33.726 --> 31:35.728
- and prove myself on the court.
- Okay.

31:35.811 --> 31:36.937
I love that.
It's very Killa B.

31:37.021 --> 31:38.147
- [Belly] Right?
- Yeah.

31:38.188 --> 31:40.858
So I don't have
to text her, right?

31:41.859 --> 31:43.444
Give me your phone.

31:44.486 --> 31:45.571
Mm...

31:45.654 --> 31:47.781
[Taylor] This is ridiculous.

31:47.865 --> 31:51.869
"Hey, Coach, I'm planning
to come to camp next weekend.

31:51.952 --> 31:54.246
I already talked
to the rest of the squad

31:54.330 --> 31:56.624
and they are cool
with me coming.

31:58.125 --> 32:00.085
Can't wait to see you
on the court."

32:00.169 --> 32:01.378
[Belly] Yeah,
that's good. Yeah.

32:01.462 --> 32:03.088
What's happening over here? Hmm?

32:03.172 --> 32:04.632
We playing Truth or Dare
or what?

32:04.715 --> 32:06.175
All right. Yeah. You in?

32:06.258 --> 32:07.593
Um...

32:09.136 --> 32:10.888
I dare you
to eat the apple bong.

32:10.929 --> 32:12.222
[chuckles]

32:14.475 --> 32:16.518
- [Taylor] Ew.
- I'm not scared.
I've done worse.

32:16.602 --> 32:17.603
Yeah, we know.

32:17.686 --> 32:18.687
We worked so hard on this.

32:18.771 --> 32:20.397
[Steven] I am so sorry, Skye.

32:20.481 --> 32:22.274
- I'm so sorry.
- [Skye] And now it's...

32:22.358 --> 32:24.610
[laughing]

32:24.693 --> 32:25.736
What does it taste like?

32:25.819 --> 32:27.613
It tastes so...

32:27.696 --> 32:28.864
[gags]

32:29.865 --> 32:31.116
Oh, my God!

32:31.200 --> 32:33.160
- [Taylor shouts]
- [Steven] Oh, my God.

32:33.243 --> 32:35.120
- Gross.
- Goddamn it!

32:35.204 --> 32:36.664
Wait, wait. He knows he's going
to have to clean that up, right?

32:36.747 --> 32:38.874
We'll make him clean it up.
We'll make him clean it up.

32:38.957 --> 32:40.709
Apple all over my leg.

32:40.793 --> 32:42.836
- [laughs]
- You guys trying to keep
playing Truth or Dare?

32:42.920 --> 32:43.962
Conrad?

32:44.046 --> 32:46.674
- I'm not playing.
- Come on, dude.

32:46.757 --> 32:47.966
- [Conrad] No.
- [Jeremiah] What, you scared?

32:48.008 --> 32:49.927
- [laughter]
- Come on, man.

32:50.010 --> 32:52.221
Where do you, uh, see yourself

32:52.304 --> 32:54.098
- in the next ten years?
- [Conrad exhales]

32:59.311 --> 33:01.188
Here, honestly.

33:02.272 --> 33:04.274
Coming back to Cousins.

33:04.358 --> 33:06.360
Fourth of July barbecues,

33:06.443 --> 33:10.239
digging for clams,
serving with Jere...

33:10.322 --> 33:12.741
- Making pomegranate margaritas.
- [Conrad] Right, right.

33:12.825 --> 33:14.118
I don't know, I just feel like

33:14.201 --> 33:15.911
whatever kind of shit
you got going on,

33:15.994 --> 33:17.705
you just come back here,
you forget about it.

33:19.415 --> 33:22.918
Come on, man. Nobody's playing
Truth or Dare right.

33:23.001 --> 33:24.837
It's either you go big
or you go home.

33:24.920 --> 33:27.506
Agreed. This needs to get
way more Euphoria.

33:27.589 --> 33:30.801
Okay. Um...
I'll give it a whirl.

33:30.884 --> 33:31.844
- Hey.
- [Taylor] Yay.

33:31.927 --> 33:34.179
- Uh...
- What you got?

33:34.263 --> 33:37.349
Belly. I dare you to, uh,

33:37.433 --> 33:39.017
kiss Jeremiah.

33:44.982 --> 33:46.859
[Jeremiah] I can remember
the exact moment

33:46.942 --> 33:48.986
when everything changed.

33:49.069 --> 33:50.946
- [♪ Niall Horan: "Heaven"]
- ♪ Strange light revolves ♪

33:51.029 --> 33:52.489
- ♪ Around you ♪
- [Steven] Oh, my God.

33:52.573 --> 33:54.408
♪ You float across the room...

33:54.491 --> 33:55.701
[Jeremiah] From the first moment
I saw her last summer,

33:55.784 --> 33:56.785
I was done for.

33:56.869 --> 33:58.287
♪ Heaven can't hold...

33:58.370 --> 34:00.581
She'd always been just Belly.

34:00.664 --> 34:03.292
A girl I've known
my whole life, my friend.

34:03.375 --> 34:05.335
Except what I was feeling
in that moment

34:05.419 --> 34:06.712
was so much stronger.

34:06.795 --> 34:07.880
- How was the drive?
- Good.

34:07.963 --> 34:09.089
- Great.
- Awesome. Hey...

34:09.172 --> 34:11.049
I wanted to grab her
and hold her

34:11.132 --> 34:12.717
and kiss the shit out of her.

34:12.760 --> 34:15.179
- And the feeling
never went away.
- Uh...

34:15.262 --> 34:17.431
Jere! Jere, Jere, Jere, Jere!
Come over here. Come on.

34:17.514 --> 34:19.641
[Jeremiah] But I wasn't
the only one.

34:19.725 --> 34:22.311
♪ God only knows ♪

34:22.393 --> 34:24.521
♪ Where this could go ♪

34:24.605 --> 34:27.357
♪ And even if our love
starts to grow...

34:27.440 --> 34:28.942
I tried to convince myself
for a long time

34:29.025 --> 34:30.319
that they weren't inevitable.

34:30.402 --> 34:32.279
[Belly] Too bad. I like me
better without them.

34:32.362 --> 34:33.989
[Jeremiah] That I had a chance.

34:34.072 --> 34:36.241
♪ Heaven won't be the same...

34:36.324 --> 34:38.577
But it's pretty clear to me now
that I never actually did.

34:38.659 --> 34:39.870
...exactly like
I thought it would.

34:43.498 --> 34:44.958
You know, aren't we too old
for that kind of shit?

34:45.042 --> 34:46.293
Right? [scoffs]

34:47.293 --> 34:48.337
- [clears throat]
- [insects trilling]

34:48.420 --> 34:49.588
[Taylor] Yeah.

34:49.670 --> 34:52.216
Cam, you know the drill.

34:52.299 --> 34:54.592
Yes. Truth, please.

34:54.676 --> 34:56.637
What's your biggest regret?

34:57.638 --> 34:59.807
- [chuckles] Um...
- [Taylor laughs]

35:01.433 --> 35:05.479
I'd probably say, um,
not spending enough time

35:05.562 --> 35:07.314
with my sister before she died.

35:07.397 --> 35:09.608
- Whoa, I'm sorry.
I didn't know.
- It's okay.

35:09.691 --> 35:11.527
- You don't have to talk
about it if you don't want to.
- [Cam] It's okay.

35:11.610 --> 35:13.237
It was ten years ago.

35:13.320 --> 35:15.364
She was 16. Um,

35:15.447 --> 35:16.740
I was just a kid.

35:16.824 --> 35:19.034
I really looked up to her.

35:19.117 --> 35:21.620
Mm, I still look up to her.

35:21.703 --> 35:23.997
Does it get any easier?

35:25.415 --> 35:26.416
Yeah.

35:28.252 --> 35:29.837
It's always there, you know.

35:29.920 --> 35:32.214
But, um...

35:32.297 --> 35:34.424
the pain starts to, uh...

35:34.508 --> 35:38.053
you know, feel more like
a scar than it does a scab.

35:38.095 --> 35:41.807
Like, sometimes something
totally random will set you off.

35:41.890 --> 35:43.559
Like, um...

35:43.642 --> 35:47.271
a song she used
to play for you or, um...

35:47.354 --> 35:51.191
little yellow tree
air fresheners

35:51.275 --> 35:53.026
she had in her car and the...

35:53.110 --> 35:55.696
pain just feels brand-new again.

35:55.779 --> 35:57.197
But, um...

35:57.281 --> 35:59.491
everything...

35:59.575 --> 36:01.285
everything goes
back to normal.

36:01.368 --> 36:03.579
Eventually.
Whatever the hell that means.

36:03.662 --> 36:05.038
Yeah, the fuck if I know.

36:05.122 --> 36:06.999
[Conrad] I'm sorry, man.

36:07.082 --> 36:09.501
No.

36:09.585 --> 36:11.128
I'm sorry about your mom.

36:11.211 --> 36:13.171
She was really cool.

36:14.172 --> 36:15.716
[yawns loudly]

36:15.799 --> 36:17.676
[laughter]

36:17.759 --> 36:19.845
Sorry, Taylor,
where did we lose you there?

36:19.928 --> 36:20.846
Oh, my God.
No, you didn't lose me at all.

36:20.929 --> 36:22.097
All right, just, like...

36:22.180 --> 36:23.724
No, I really love talking
about mental health.

36:23.807 --> 36:24.725
Like, you should
look at my TikTok.

36:24.808 --> 36:26.685
It's, like, 70% therapists.

36:26.768 --> 36:29.563
I'm just, like,
really fucking tired right now.

36:29.646 --> 36:32.107
Yeah, I guess it is
getting kind of late.

36:32.190 --> 36:34.693
I'll, uh, I'll go get you
some blankets.

36:34.776 --> 36:37.112
- [Jeremiah] Yeah, let's do it.
- [Cam] Yep.

36:37.195 --> 36:38.530
[Taylor] Is this camping?
'Cause I got

36:38.614 --> 36:39.823
a badge for that shit
in Girl Scouts.

36:39.907 --> 36:41.283
[Jeremiah] Gonna take my leave.

36:41.366 --> 36:43.827
[Taylor] Did anyone find
an air mattress, by chance?

36:43.911 --> 36:45.913
[insects trilling]

36:50.918 --> 36:52.210
Hey, um...

36:55.756 --> 36:58.759
I'm, uh, I'm sorry
if the dancing thing was weird.

36:58.842 --> 37:00.260
It wasn't weird.

37:00.344 --> 37:03.513
I mean, it was,
but I didn't hate it.

37:04.598 --> 37:06.975
Bad bitches
need their roses, too.

37:07.059 --> 37:08.894
You know?

37:08.977 --> 37:11.021
I'll take your word for it.

37:11.104 --> 37:13.440
- [Taylor] You know what I mean.
- Yeah, sure.

37:21.907 --> 37:23.575
[sighs]

37:27.329 --> 37:29.915
♪ ♪

37:49.059 --> 37:51.019
♪ ♪

37:57.484 --> 38:00.112
[Steven and Taylor
chat quietly]

38:00.195 --> 38:02.197
[Taylor giggles]

38:08.620 --> 38:10.580
Hey.

38:10.664 --> 38:12.582
[Belly] You want to go
finish the movie?

38:13.583 --> 38:15.168
It's kind of late.

38:15.210 --> 38:17.295
[sighs]

38:17.379 --> 38:19.131
Do I have BO or something?

38:19.214 --> 38:21.675
I mean,
I've never seen you turn down

38:21.758 --> 38:23.176
a Truth or Dare kiss before.

38:23.260 --> 38:25.262
Don't-don't do that.

38:26.304 --> 38:29.641
Do what? I'm just trying
to talk to you.

38:29.725 --> 38:31.393
I mean, before,
on the, on the boardwalk...

38:31.476 --> 38:32.728
Just stop.

38:33.770 --> 38:35.647
Okay?

38:35.731 --> 38:36.690
[Belly] Why?

38:36.773 --> 38:38.608
[Jeremiah sighs]

38:38.692 --> 38:41.194
Why don't you want to kiss me?

38:45.282 --> 38:48.076
Because if I kiss you, I don't
know that I can ever stop.

38:52.330 --> 38:53.623
[Susannah] I'm sorry,
Laurel, but you suck

38:53.707 --> 38:55.625
- at taking pictures.
- [Laurel laughs on video call]

38:55.709 --> 38:57.794
I just wish I could be
with you guys. [laughs]

38:59.171 --> 39:01.465
[Belly] I'll make sure she
gets some good ones, Susannah.

39:01.548 --> 39:03.175
[whispers] Don't let it sit
too long.

39:03.258 --> 39:05.302
[whispers] Thank you.

39:05.385 --> 39:08.680
Okay, now I-I want one with-with
all the girls together.

39:08.764 --> 39:10.223
- [camera shutter clicks]
- [Jeremiah] I was annoyed

39:10.307 --> 39:11.600
with Conrad that day,

39:11.683 --> 39:14.019
with everything about him.

39:14.102 --> 39:15.812
He'd gotten to take Belly
to her prom,

39:15.896 --> 39:18.273
